Shenzhen – China Southern Airlines says it will reopen Shenzhen-Bangkok airline services from March 13. The airline said on Thursday, that the flight would be the company’s first resumed international flight departing from Shenzhen following a large-scale suspension of flights caused by the coronavirus outbreak. According to the company’s Shenzhen branch, the restored round-trip flight will be operated on Airbus A320 daily. “China Southern Airlines has made plans to restart more than 460 domestic and international flights departing from Shenzhen. “Suspended flights will be restored at an accelerated pace,’’ the airline said. (Xinhua/NAN)